</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B93F21BFF877854BF87FE09FD74FDC0" blockId="3.[189,692,599,625]" box="[189,692,599,625]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="B9582E09FF877854BF87FE09FEF6FDC0" bold="true" box="[189,310,599,625]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(modified from 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD8FEAFF877854BECDFE09FD6CFDC0" author="Borowski C." box="[503,684,599,625]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="129 - 144" refId="ref6969" refString="Borowski C. 1994. New records of Longosomatidae (Heterospionidae) (Annelida, Polychaeta) from the abyssal Southeast Pacific, with the description of Heterospio peruana sp. nov. and a general remark on the family. Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut 92 (Suppl. 1): 129 - 144." type="journal article" year="1994">Borowski 1994</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B93F21BFF877854BF87FEDBFB8AFC08" blockId="3.[189,1399,645,954]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Body elongated, linear, divided in three regions. Anterior region with 6̅8 short chaetigers; median region with greatly elongated segments; posterior region with few short, inflated segments. Posterior part of prostomium with a pair of lateral nuchal organs. Proboscis eversible, epithelial pouch. One pair of grooved peristomial palps, easily lost, leaving scars on lateral surfaces. Anterior region with 3–8 pairs of cirriform branchiae, usually very long, one pair per segment, arising above notopodia, beginning from chaetiger 2. Anterior region with biramous parapodia provided with simple capillaries, with or without acicular spines; elongated segments with chaetae usually forming a cincture near anterior margin; chaetae simple capillaries, may be accompanied by subuluncini, aristae chaetae, and acicular spines; posteriormost inflated chaetigers provided with strong acicular hooks.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C336A190FF877854BF87FFBFFB56FAF2" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B93F21BFF877854BF87FFBFFEEFFC4A" blockId="3.[189,303,993,1019]" box="[189,303,993,1019]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading id="D0DB4577FF877854BF87FFBFFEEFFC4A" bold="true" box="[189,303,993,1019]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9582E09FF877854BF87FFBFFEEFFC4A" bold="true" box="[189,303,993,1019]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B93F21BFF877854BF87F851FB56FAF2" blockId="3.[189,1399,1039,1347]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Following 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD8FEAFF877854BE05F84EFDF7FB98" author="Parapar J. &amp; Aguirrezabalaga F. &amp; Moreira J." box="[319,567,1039,1066]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="983 - 998" refId="ref7437" refString="Parapar J., Aguirrezabalaga F. &amp; Moreira J. 2014. First record of Longosomatidae (Annelida: Polychaeta) from Iceland with a worldwide review of diagnostic characters of the family. Journal of Natural History 48: 983 - 998. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222933.2013.859316" type="journal article" year="2014">
Parapar 
<emphasis id="B9582E09FF877854BE9BF84EFE1EFB98" box="[417,478,1039,1065]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
, the terms “thorax” and “abdomen” are not used in the diagnosis due to the lack of a clear criterion about their limits. The presence of nuchal organs on the prostomium was included in the diagnosis. The range of 7̅9 short anterior chaetigers provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD8FEAFF877854BBAAF80BFA99FBC1" author="Borowski C." box="[1168,1369,1109,1136]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="129 - 144" refId="ref6969" refString="Borowski C. 1994. New records of Longosomatidae (Heterospionidae) (Annelida, Polychaeta) from the abyssal Southeast Pacific, with the description of Heterospio peruana sp. nov. and a general remark on the family. Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut 92 (Suppl. 1): 129 - 144." type="journal article" year="1994">Borowski (1994)</bibRefCitation>
is modified to 6̅8, following 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD8FEAFF877854BEC5F827FD32FB22" author="Parapar J. &amp; Aguirrezabalaga F. &amp; Moreira J." box="[511,754,1145,1171]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="983 - 998" refId="ref7437" refString="Parapar J., Aguirrezabalaga F. &amp; Moreira J. 2014. First record of Longosomatidae (Annelida: Polychaeta) from Iceland with a worldwide review of diagnostic characters of the family. Journal of Natural History 48: 983 - 998. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222933.2013.859316" type="journal article" year="2014">
Parapar 
<emphasis id="B9582E09FF877854BD65F827FD59FB22" box="[607,665,1145,1171]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
. Peristomial palps were qualified as “easily deciduous” because they are not reported in most descriptions. More details are provided about the number (range) and size of branchiae. The term “parapodia biramous” is used here only for anterior segments; it is also highlighted that in elongated segments there may be a change in the arrangement of chaetae, i.e., forming cinctures, although those seem not be present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C8998FF877854BCBBF958FB0CFA91" authority="Ehlers, 1874" authorityName="Ehlers" authorityYear="1874" box="[897,1228,1285,1312]" class="Polychaeta" family="Longosomatidae" genus="Heterospio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spionida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="longissima">
<emphasis id="B9582E09FF877854BCBBF958FBE8FAAE" box="[897,1064,1285,1311]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">H. longissima</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD8FEAFF877854BB0EF95BFB0CFA91" author="Ehlers E." box="[1076,1228,1285,1312]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="292 - 298" refId="ref7029" refString="Ehlers E. 1874. Annulata nova vel minus cognita in Expeditione &quot; Porcupine &quot; capta. The Annals and Magazine of Natural history, Ser. 4. 13: 292 - 298. Available from http: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 24342680 [accessed 6 Jul. 2016]" type="journal article" year="1874">Ehlers, 1874</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9582E09FF877854BBE2F958FAAFFAAE" box="[1240,1391,1286,1311]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26B9372FF877854BBE2F958FAAFFAAE" box="[1240,1391,1286,1311]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" sensu="stricto">sensu stricto</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C8998FF877854BF87F977FD75FAF2" authority="Laubier, Picard &amp; Ramos, 1973" authorityName="Laubier, Picard &amp; Ramos" authorityYear="1973" box="[189,693,1321,1347]" class="Polychaeta" family="Longosomatidae" genus="Heterospio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spionida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="reducta">
<emphasis id="B9582E09FF877854BF87F977FF1AFAF3" box="[189,218,1321,1346]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">H.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B9582E09FF877854BFDBF977FEFAFAF2" box="[225,314,1321,1347]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">reducta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD8FEAFF877854BE7BF977FD75FAF2" author="Laubier L. &amp; Picard C. &amp; Ramos J." box="[321,693,1321,1347]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="243 - 254" refId="ref7269" refString="Laubier L., Picard C. &amp; Ramos J. 1973. Les Heterospionidae (Annelides polychaetes sedentaires) de Mediterranee Occidentale. Vie et Milieu 23: 243 - 254." type="journal article" year="1973">Laubier, Picard &amp; Ramos, 1973</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C8998FF877854BDE6F977FB52FAF2" authority="Bochert &amp; Zettler, 2009" authorityName="Bochert &amp; Zettler" authorityYear="2009" box="[732,1170,1321,1347]" class="Polychaeta" family="Longosomatidae" genus="Heterospio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spionida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="angolana">
<emphasis id="B9582E09FF877854BDE6F977FD39FAF3" box="[732,761,1321,1346]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">H.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B9582E09FF877854BC3AF977FCAFFAF2" box="[768,879,1321,1347]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">angolana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD8FEAFF877854BC4CF977FB52FAF2" author="Bochert R. &amp; Zettler M. L." box="[886,1170,1321,1347]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="735 - 737" refId="ref6919" refString="Bochert R. &amp; Zettler M. L. 2009. A new species of Heterospio (Polychaeta, Longosomatidae) from offshore Angola. Zoological Science 26 (10): 735 - 737. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2108 / zsj. 26.735" type="journal article" year="2009">Bochert &amp; Zettler, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
